{"body": "Aaron\r\n\r\nI agree 100% (and I was just being cynical when talking about compatibility). FWIW, I think the answer is actually to slowly deprecate both first and last, because the names are really not appropriate to a relational wrapper. Replace both with the method row(), or one_row(), or whatever. The deprecation warning for first() could be \"replace with .one_row.order(<the order you want>)\" and for last() you just add in a \"desc\"\r\n\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4644523", "created_at": "2012-03-22T18:00:04Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5153#issuecomment-4644523", "updated_at": "2012-03-22T18:00:04Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5153, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/pragdave", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5d06917e13b29bcff1c1609492c06873?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fb59f635e9f984164bf71aa36a8dd265e.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/received_events", "gravatar_id": "5d06917e13b29bcff1c1609492c06873", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "pragdave", "type": "User", "id": 10648, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pragdave/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523ee96cbd354364b90138d7"}, "id": 4644523, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5153"}
